{"Body": "<p>\n<div style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 8px;\">\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 2em;\">\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.996099989162758\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Tuesday the 16th&rsquo;s Students&rsquo; Union Council meeting saw Max Sullivan, creator of the anti-USI &ldquo;National Go To College Day&rdquo; Facebook event, raise the question of whether TCDSU should break affiliation with the Union of Students of Ireland, as he claimed that &ldquo;their view of economics and politics is overly focused on education&rdquo; and that they do not truly operate with a unanimous mandate from students.&rdquo; Mr Sullivan argued that the USI&rsquo;s total opposition to fees is unrealistic in the current economic climate and criticised their unwillingness to compromise.</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">USI President Gary Redmond and Deputy President C&oacute;n&aacute;n &Oacute; Broin were both in attendance, and in response to Sullivan&rsquo;s points, &Oacute; Broin made the point that &ldquo;any single students&rsquo; union on its own does not have the clout to pull off what happened [in reference to the student protest on November 3rd], and it would not have been possible without the USI&rdquo;.</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">TCDSU sabbatical officers also defended affiliation with USI, as welfare officer Steph Fleming said &ldquo;The government would still listen to the USI as a representative of all students,&rdquo; and education officer Jen Fox said &ldquo;we don&rsquo;t have to do what USI do&hellip; We decide what they do.&rdquo; TCDSU President Nikolai Trigoub-Rotnem also defended the USI, saying that &ldquo; if you see Gary Redmond or C&oacute;n&aacute;n &Oacute; Broin walking across campus wearing suits, it&rsquo;s because they&rsquo;re walking to the D&aacute;il to defend students&rsquo; interests.&rdquo; </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Gary Redmond, USI President, also spoke, calling on students to &ldquo;continue the pressure on TDs, we are the future of this country, and we are the future tax payers, unity is strength.&rdquo;</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Max Sullivan spoke again, and said that he found the USI presence was &ldquo;slightly objectionable&rdquo; and that &ldquo;if we have a protective grant, there is no reason not to introduce fees.&rdquo; A procedural motion to add a motion to the agenda which would see students vote on whether to hold a referendum on USI affiliation was roundly rejected by class representatives.</span></div>\n</h1>\n</div>\n</p>", "Imageurl": "<p>\n<div style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 8px;\">\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 2em;\">\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.996099989162758\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Tuesday the 16th&rsquo;s Students&rsquo; Union Council meeting saw Max Sullivan, creator of the anti-USI &ldquo;National Go To College Day&rdquo; Facebook event, raise the question of whether TCDSU should break affiliation with the Union of Students of Ireland, as he claimed that &ldquo;their view of economics and politics is overly focused on education&rdquo; and that they do not truly operate with a unanimous mandate from students.&rdquo; Mr Sullivan argued that the USI&rsquo;s total opposition to fees is unrealistic in the current economic climate and criticised their unwillingness to compromise.</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">USI President Gary Redmond and Deputy President C&oacute;n&aacute;n &Oacute; Broin were both in attendance, and in response to Sullivan&rsquo;s points, &Oacute; Broin made the point that &ldquo;any single students&rsquo; union on its own does not have the clout to pull off what happened [in reference to the student protest on November 3rd], and it would not have been possible without the USI&rdquo;.</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">TCDSU sabbatical officers also defended affiliation with USI, as welfare officer Steph Fleming said &ldquo;The government would still listen to the USI as a representative of all students,&rdquo; and education officer Jen Fox said &ldquo;we don&rsquo;t have to do what USI do&hellip; We decide what they do.&rdquo; TCDSU President Nikolai Trigoub-Rotnem also defended the USI, saying that &ldquo; if you see Gary Redmond or C&oacute;n&aacute;n &Oacute; Broin walking across campus wearing suits, it&rsquo;s because they&rsquo;re walking to the D&aacute;il to defend students&rsquo; interests.&rdquo; </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Gary Redmond, USI President, also spoke, calling on students to &ldquo;continue the pressure on TDs, we are the future of this country, and we are the future tax payers, unity is strength.&rdquo;</span></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Times; font-weight: normal; font-size: medium; margin: 0px;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Max Sullivan spoke again, and said that he found the USI presence was &ldquo;slightly objectionable&rdquo; and that &ldquo;if we have a protective grant, there is no reason not to introduce fees.&rdquo; A procedural motion to add a motion to the agenda which would see students vote on whether to hold a referendum on USI affiliation was roundly rejected by class representatives.</span></div>\n</h1>\n</div>\n</p>", "Thumb_nail": "http://universitytimes.ie/wp-content/uploads/2013/utlogo.jpg", "ID": "793", "Heading": "SU debates USI affiliation"}